<p>A distribution is heavy-tailed when there are more chances to get large
values. Consequently, the variance is higher and will make the mean
misleading as many outliers have high values. Below are p.d.f.
(light-tailed and heavy-tailed</p>

<p><img src="/assets/img/heavy-light-tailed.png" alt="image" height="20%" width="50%" /></p>

<p>An real-life example of heavy-tailed distribution is the income in the
US.</p>
